Sentencas: Solid oxide fuel cell (SOFC) that is capable to operate on both hydrogen and methane as fuels is desired and its anode receives particular attention since it is the cell component directly converting fuels.
Titulo: A high power density solid oxide fuel cell based on nano-structured La0.8Sr0.2Cr0.5Fe0.5O3-δ anode

Sentencas: (La,Sr) CrFeO3-delta is regarded as a candidate anode material but its electrochemical performance has been unsatisfactory.
Titulo: A high power density solid oxide fuel cell based on nano-structured La0.8Sr0.2Cr0.5Fe0.5O3-δ anode

Sentencas: In this study, we improved the performance of an SOFC based exclusively on a La0.8Sr0.2Cr0.5Fe0.5O3-delta anode by means of impregnation.
Titulo: A high power density solid oxide fuel cell based on nano-structured La0.8Sr0.2Cr0.5Fe0.5O3-δ anode

Sentencas: At 800 degrees C, the maximum power densities of such a cell reach 846 mWcm(-2) with hydrogen as fuel, and 117 mW cm(-2) when methane is fed.
